<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="182" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.9318.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Hale</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 2, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram of August 25. The Chinese Government requests the United
                            States to exercise its good offices in behalf of Chinese in Costa Rica.
                            You will inquire of the Costa Rican Government whether this will be
                            agreeable and if so in case of need you will use your good offices in
                            behalf of Chinese residents and instruct American consuls to do the
                            same.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>